	                Sponsorship
























								Aberdeen proudly sponsors Extreme Sailing Series™ - Singapore




In partnership with the Singapore Sports Council and the Singapore Tourism Board, Extreme Sailing Series™ (ESS) signed a three-year deal to stage the Extreme Sailing Series in Singapore from 2013-2015 .
Aberdeen is proud to participate as the event main partner for this period. Last year we brought in ‘Team Aberdeen Singapore’ with a couple of Singapore’s most promising young sailors on board; this year they competed against the world’s best.
A brand new international fixture on the Singapore sports calendar, the Extreme Sailing Series features fleets of at least eight international teams competing in identical Extreme 40s catamarans against the skyline of Singapore Marina Bay. The event is part of an eight-act global tour spanning Asia, Europe and the Middle East.
Videos and event photos for 2015
Highlight: Team Aberdeen in Extreme Sailing Series 2015
Team Aberdeen Singapore and seven other boats competed for line honours in Act 1 of the Extreme Sailing Series in Singapore over February 6-8. With the event into its third year, it's clear Singapore has taken to the Extremes.

Extreme Sailing SeriesTM videos - Relive the excitement of Act 1 2015 from the Extreme Sailing SeriesTM
Extreme Sailing SeriesTM Act 1, Singapore - Day 3 low down

Extreme Sailing SeriesTM Act 1, Singapore: Day 2 round up

Photo gallery
 
About ESS — Extreme Sailing Series
Since 2007, the award-winning Extreme Sailing SeriesTM has become a benchmark in the sailing world, steadily growing and attracting the biggest names in the sport.
With some of the most respected skippers helming state-of-the-art multihulls on demanding courses, the creators of the Extreme Sailing SeriesTM have set new standards, both in terms of high level competition and sporting entertainment.
Uniquely, spectators get to see all the action close-up because of the use of tight courses close to shore. Singapore Marina Bay is the perfect stadium!












