								Fixed Income




How we invest
Global expertise, local insight and fundamental research underpin our fixed income process. We create long-term value by running high conviction portfolios informed by our own security analysis. We don’t chase yield and see loss avoidance as more crucial to returns than identifying winners.
Key points:

Global reach with experienced teams around the world
Own in-depth, forward-looking research
Security focus on value relative to fundamental quality
Emphasis on risk oversight to reduce losses and protect income
Longstanding Asian presence supports insight into emerging markets

 





















                    What sets us apart?
Fundamental research
We believe fundamental analysis is key to creating long-term value. This demands first-hand research coupled with a clear, disciplined approach to value and risk.
Our teams in North America, Europe and Asia Pacific enable us to cover the bond market in extraordinary depth, with research into government bonds, currencies, credit and asset-backed securities including investment grade, high yield, convertible and loan markets. Our macro analysts cover the majority of country issuers worldwide.
Discipline on valuations
As most fixed income securities have limited upside, our investment analysis starts with a valuation framework, with price targets for all the investments in the portfolio.
A strong buy and sell discipline means we consistently seek to add attractive securities into our portfolios and reduce our holding of expensive ones.
A standardised approach to risk
To achieve strong risk-adjusted returns, we use a set of measures that enhance our ability to assess the investment upside together with downside risk in our portfolios.

*Please note that the content on this page refers to Aberdeen globally, while Aberdeen Asset Management Asia Limited Shanghai Representative Office does not make any investment, provide any investment advice, or develop, distribute or sell any investment products.









